It’s a flimsy argument. To begin with, the new process is more in line with the way companies used to go public. For instance, Apple Computer (as it was known early on) filed its S-1 on November 6, 1980. It went public on December 12th. Microsoft filed its S-1 on February 3, 1986, and went public on March 13th.
